title: For Sale/Trade:  SCAM ALERT
postcontent:
Here's another scammer:

Message from: REDACTED

Message regarding: Shotgun 

Hi there, i am interested in this arm on  arms list Lemme know you still have it?

And:

Daniel Steve [REDACTED]

Re: ARMSLIST - Message from REDACTED about Shotgun

Thanks for the response i will mail a check for the Payment of the arm. You need to send me your Full contact information. Such has your name,address,city,state and postal code,once i received that, i will mail check ASAP once the check is received and clears your account i will send my shipper to come and pick up the item at your residence after the check has been credited in to your account.Lemme know

Things to watch out for:

Poor English

Request for Personal Information

Asking questions already answered in the ad

Offer to send a check of some sort

Offer to arrange a shipper to make pick up later

Usually this will drag on for a while, and will involve the "buyer" wanting to send a much larger check than required, and of course wanting you to return the difference. They don't even want your property, they only want you to cash their phoney check against your bank account, and cheat you out of your own money in the form of a "refund". You will end up getting ripped off for however much you give them. Most banks will verify funds before cashing any check, but if you've been with them a while they may cut you some slack, and only help you to get scammed.

Be careful and good luck.

title: For Sale/Trade:  800 Rounds Federal HST .40S&W JHP
postcontent:
Best CCW Ammo you can buy!

For sale/trade is 800 rounds of Federal HST 155gr JHP for a .40S&W. Current retail price on this is between $1.25/round and $1.50/round - I am only asking $1.00 per round for cash offers.

Federal released its Hydra-Shok line of ammunition to capture the law enforcement market years ago, and while it was a good round - it proved troublesome when going through barriers before reaching its target - clogging much of the time.

Federal corrected the problem by introducing a line known as HST, and it was tested extensively by the FBI upon its release in .40 caliber, and adopted as their ammunition after blowing the tests out of the water. This is currently the only ammunition I will carry as I feel like it is the only ammunition to hold a candle to the famous "Black Talon".

It's easy to find the much less desirable Hydra-Shok ammunition on the shelf, and many people are intrigued by the "post" inside the hollow point. If you do the research, and I suggest you do, you will find that HST is extremely tough to beat.

That's why HST has almost never (in my experience) been for sale on the shelves at your local gun shop - I have only ever found it online, for a premium price, and in small or limited quantities. I have recently switched to a different caliber for my preferred CCW and cannot find anywhere that sells HST in bulk, must less a place with a single box in stock right now.

I live in Puyallup, but will be willing to drive a reasonable distance to meet - or even ship if you want to pay for shipping.

Take a look here for FBI Protocol test results on this ammunition
http://le.atk.com/ammunition/federal/handgun/details.aspx?id=567

title: For Sale:  Brand New!!!! CMMG Rifle, AR15, 5.56, 16" CM, M4, FSB
postcontent:
W.A.S.P. Treated Barrel
(Weapon Armament Surface Protection) is a salt bath ferritic nitrocarburizing surface conversion process or more commonly referred to as nitriding. The nitriding conversion is applied to the barrel inside and out, along with the front sight base on our LE rifles and uppers. Nitriding offers improved wear, abrasion, and corrosion resistance when compared to hard chrome lining or phosphating.

Unlike chrome lining, where the chrome is built up on the surface, nitriding converts the surface without the risk of dimensional build up. CMMG Pioneered the use of this nitriding process on AR barrels and has been using it for many years.

LIFETIME GUARANTEE

title: For Sale:  Winchester 1895 - 100 Years of Conservation - US Forest Service
postcontent: Winchester 1895 - 100 Years of Conservation - US Forest Service, Tongass National Forest Centennial Rifle in 405 Winchester, 1 of 100 manufactured in 2002, 24" barrel, brand new in its box. The engraved figures illustrate a number of Tongass National Forest characteristics and historic features. On one side of the receiver, you see the Tongass National Forest and the centennial dates. Teddy smiling at you, looking “Bully.” An eagle soars, a bear starring at you above the trigger, the magazine reads, “Big Medicine,” the name Teddy gave his .405 on his African hunt in 1909. On the other side of the receiver, you see “Seventeen of One Hundred” among filigreed vines embellishing the magazine. Above it on the left floats a Forest Service ranger boat, the “Tongass Ranger.”  To the left of the Tongass Ranger is a totem pole, representative of the traditionally close ties the forest has to the Tlingit, Haida, and Tsimshian peoples. To the right of the Tongass Ranger is the Forest Service shield. And higher up on the receiver is the recognition that the Forest Service has been engaged in “100 Years of Conservation” on the Tongass National Forest. Absolutely a beautiful gun, and I may add very rare with only 100 being produced.
